mibdebugProfileTable.name: mibdebugProfileTable
mibdebugProfileTable.description: A list of mibdebugProfile profile entries.

mibdebugProfileEntry.name: mibdebugProfileEntry
mibdebugProfileEntry.description: A mibdebugProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibdebugProfile profile.

debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf.name: debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot.name: debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot
debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber.name: debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
debugProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

debugProfile_Active.name: debugProfile_Active
debugProfile_Active.description: Setting this field to Yes enables this profile. Setting this field to No disables this entire profile.

debugProfile_EnableCoreDump.name: debugProfile_EnableCoreDump
debugProfile_EnableCoreDump.description: Core dump on system failure can be enabled by setting this field to Yes. Core dumps are disabled if this field is No.

debugProfile_CoreDumpServer.name: debugProfile_CoreDumpServer
debugProfile_CoreDumpServer.description: The name (or IP address) of the host setup to receive our core dumps.

debugProfile_EnableGdb.name: debugProfile_EnableGdb
debugProfile_EnableGdb.description: GDB can be enabled by setting this field to Yes. GDB is disabled if this field is No.

debugProfile_GdbHost.name: debugProfile_GdbHost
debugProfile_GdbHost.description: The name (or IP address) of the host running GDB.

debugProfile_CsTracking.name: debugProfile_CsTracking
debugProfile_CsTracking.description: csTracking can be enabled by setting this field to Yes. csTracking is disabled if this field is No.

debugProfile_GenericField.name: debugProfile_GenericField
debugProfile_GenericField.description: This field can be used as a generic bitmask stored in nonvolatile memory and thus preserved over resets and powerdowns

debugProfile_MinWarningCoreDump.name: debugProfile_MinWarningCoreDump
debugProfile_MinWarningCoreDump.description: Minimum value for a range of warning numbers that will generate a core dump (a core dump is taken for warnings between the minimum and maximum warning numbers inclusive) if coredumps are enabled. The default value of 0 in the minimum and maximum fields mean that only warnings from 101 to 121 will cause a core dump.

debugProfile_MaxWarningCoreDump.name: debugProfile_MaxWarningCoreDump
debugProfile_MaxWarningCoreDump.description: Maximum value for a range of warning numbers that will generate a core dump (a core dump is taken for warnings between the minimum and maximum warning numbers inclusive) if coredumps are enabled. The default value of 0 in the minimum and maximum fields mean that only warnings from 101 to 121 will cause a core dump.

debugProfile_CoreDumpLocation.name: debugProfile_CoreDumpLocation
debugProfile_CoreDumpLocation.description: Core dumps will go to the specified location if enabled.

debugProfile_FlashCoreOverwrite.name: debugProfile_FlashCoreOverwrite
debugProfile_FlashCoreOverwrite.description: A previous flash dump will be overwritten by a new dump if this field to Yes, but will be preserved if this field is No.

debugProfile_CoreDumpRipUpdate.name: debugProfile_CoreDumpRipUpdate
debugProfile_CoreDumpRipUpdate.description: RIP updates will be sent accordingly based on the setting here during coredump.

debugProfile_CoredumpSourceAddress.name: debugProfile_CoredumpSourceAddress
debugProfile_CoredumpSourceAddress.description: The coredump source ip address for the shelf card. It is usually set only if the system-ip-address and the coredump server ip address belong to different networks.
